utions upon itrons acquisition of silicon energy in  mezey joined the company as managing director of software development for itrons energy management solutions group prior to joining silicon energy in  as vice president software development mezey was a founding member and served  years with indus a provider of integrated asset and customer management software mezey earned his ba degree in history from the university of california berkeley learn about the rest of itrons leadership team corporate  sustainability report view our latest corporate sustainability report download report powering the next generation solving the energy and water challenges of tomorrow will require fresh thinking and new perspectives education plays a critical role in our ability to raise awareness and inspire the next generation of problem solvers to help create a more resourceful world read more resourcefulness an introduction to the energywater nexus is mobile device compatible with rapid changes in technologies and an aging workforce we are facing a significant skills gap in stem related fields of study science technology engineering and math as a business leader and stem employer itron is partnering with dr michael webber renowned author and professor at the university of texas at austin to invest in the next generation of innovators to help solve the world’s greatest challenges our resourcefulness an introduction to the energywater nexus is being created in line with college and career readinesscommon core standards including next generation science standards advanced placement ap environmental science and international baccalaureate environmental systems and societies the material is designed to complement and enhance existing curriculum and lesson plans with fully developed teaching resources over the coming months resourcefulness will evolve from a more traditional inclass educational program for secondary education into a curriculum that can be shared across many channels modular 